        },
        "category": [
          {
            "coding": [
              {
                "system": "urn:virpat:fhir:doc-type",
                "code": "patient-description"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} is a 39-year-old woman with a warm but perpetually busy demeanor. She works as a mid-level marketing manager at a fast-paced advertising agency, where deadlines, client calls, and long hours are the norm. She often skips lunch or eats hurriedly at her desk, relying on strong black coffee — sometimes three to four cups a day — to power through her schedule. In the evenings, she tends to unwind with a glass of red wine and a late dinner, often past 9 PM, before heading to bed within an hour or two. She is of average build, standing 165 cm tall and weighing 72 kg, with a slightly anxious appearance and occasional dark circles under her eyes from disrupted sleep. {patientName} enjoys weekend hiking and yoga, though her irregular schedule makes consistent exercise difficult. She lives with her husband and two school-age children, and the household rhythm keeps her perpetually on the go. She has complained to her family doctor about a persistent burning sensation rising from her stomach into her chest and throat, particularly at night and after large meals. She describes a frequent sour taste in her mouth upon waking, occasional regurgitation, and a nagging dry cough that has worried her. The symptoms have been present on and off for nearly two years but have worsened in recent months, interfering with her sleep and concentration at work."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "fullUrl": "urn:uuid:6248c212-d48e-4bb6-aa33-1701341b6e3e",
      "resource": {
        "resourceType": "Communication",
        "status": "completed",
        "text": {
          "status": "generated",
          "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">patient-history</div>"
        },
        "category": [
          {
            "coding": [
              {
                "system": "urn:virpat:fhir:doc-type",
                "code": "patient-history"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} has no prior hospitalizations. She has a background of mild anxiety managed without pharmacotherapy. She was diagnosed with irritable bowel syndrome (IBS) at age 33, managed with dietary modifications. She has a BMI of approximately 26.4 (mildly overweight). She is a non-smoker but drinks alcohol socially (3–5 units/week). She reports a high-caffeine diet and irregular meal timing. She is currently not on any hormonal contraception. She has a known allergy to Penicillin causing a skin rash. Family history is notable for peptic ulcer disease in her father and colorectal cancer in her maternal grandmother, and GORD in her mother. {patientName} reports GORD-like symptoms worsening with stress and premenstrually. She has never undergone formal endoscopy prior to this presentation. Her symptoms score high on validated GORD questionnaires, and empiric proton pump inhibitor (PPI) therapy produced partial symptom relief."
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ]
